&lt;p&gt;Full Time Band 6 Renal Vasculitis Clinical Nurse Specialist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting new opportunity for a Vasculitis Clinical Nurse Specialist has arisen, based in the Kidney Unit at the Royal Stoke University Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, innovative and dynamic nurse to provide quality care and improve outcomes for adults referred to the renal vasculitis service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ideally you will have 2 years recent renal or equivalent experience and have a commitment to develop your skills in this speciality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role requires excellent communication skills to help co-ordinate the care of patients with complex health care needs. This role will involve providing education, advice and support to newly diagnosed and relapsing patients with conditions including ANCA vasculitis and glomerulonephritis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to review patients face to face and via the telephone with advice and support from medical colleagues. In addition you will act as a clinical resource to the wider immune mediated renal team and liaising with primary care where joint management of the patient pathway is indicated. Non-medical prescribing qualification and health assessment qualification would be advantageous or the willingness to work towards this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supported to access training and development opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need: Current NMC registration, evidence of study at degree level (or working towards) in Health/Nursing Related Studies. Formal leadership and an, ENB 998 or equivalent is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Minimum of 2 years post registration experience in Renal nursing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As well as a challenging this is an exciting new and rewarding role which offers many opportunities to further develop and consolidate your knowledge and clinical skills in this specialised area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
